<h1 id="redbrick-ai-sdk-and-cli">RedBrick AI SDK and CLI<a
href="#redbrick-ai-sdk-and-cli" class="headerlink"
title="Link to this heading">#</a></h1>
<p>RedBrick AI is a SaaS platform for annotating medical images.
RedBrick AI provides web based annotation tools, quality control
capabilities, collaboration tools, and SDK/CLI to integrate with
MLOps.</p>
<div class="admonition important">
<p>Important</p>
<p>Please visit our <a href="https://redbrickai.com"
class="reference external">website</a> to learn more about RedBrick AI,
or request for a free-trial. You can visit the platform documentation
here <a href="https://docs.redbrickai.com/"
class="reference external">https://docs.redbrickai.com/</a>.</p>
</div>
<p>The RedBrick AI SDK and CLI are useful for managing data IO
operations, and programmatically interacting with the application. The
CLI is best for simple operations like import and export; whereas, the
SDK is best for complex operations like importing annotations, searching
through data, etc.</p>
<p><strong>Installation</strong></p>
<p>The SDK and CLI are available on PyPI and can be installed using
pip.</p>
<div class="highlight-bash notranslate">
<div class="highlight">
<pre><code>$ pip install redbrick-sdk</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Authentication</strong></p>
<p>To use the SDK and CLI, you need a API key. You can fetch the API key
from the RedBrick AI dashboard, found on the right sidebar ‚ÄúAPI
keys‚Äù.</p>
<img src="/assets/images/sdk/api.png" alt="/assets/images/sdk/api.png" />
<p><strong>Organization and project ID‚Äôs</strong></p>
<p>For most methods in the CLI and SDK you will need a Project and/or
Organization ID. These can be found from the URL.</p>
<img src="/assets/images/sdk/ids.webp" alt="/assets/images/sdk/ids.webp" />
<h2 id="python-sdk">Python SDK<a href="#python-sdk" class="headerlink"
title="Link to this heading">#</a></h2>
<p>The SDK is best for writing Python scripts to interact with your
RedBrick AI organization &amp; projects. The SDK offers granular
functions for programmatically manipulating data, importing annotations,
assigning tasks, and more.</p>

class="sd-card sd-sphinx-override sd-mb-3 sd-shadow-sm sd-card-hover docutils">
